# RELEASE — libreoffice-uninstaller

Version:  v1.0
Date:     2026-04-04
Platform: openSUSE Tumbleweed (RPM-based)
Script:   /usr/local/bin/remove-libreoffice

---

## What's in this release

### Complete rewrite of the removal script
- Dynamic package detection via `rpm -qa` — no hardcoded package list
- Detects and removes all LibreOffice packages matching `libreoffice*` and `liblibreoffice*`
- Orphaned library cleanup — removes residual dependencies left after main package removal
- Root check with clear error message if run without privileges
- Dry-run output before removal — shows what will be removed

### Installation
- Script installed as `/usr/local/bin/remove-libreoffice` — no `./` prefix, no extension
- Executable directly from any terminal: `sudo remove-libreoffice`

### Compatibility
- Tested on openSUSE Tumbleweed with Squid/zypper package management
- Works with any LibreOffice version installed via zypper or RPM

### Documentation
- README rewritten — problem statement, installation, usage examples
- `CONTRIBUTING.md` — contribution guidelines
